cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.SN, cs.DS, cs.NI 

The paper deals with the identification of influential nodes in networks, which is a common topic in social network analysis (cs.SI), system dynamics (cs.SY), network science (cs.SN), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The proposed centrality measures are based on simulations, which involve the use of network models and algorithms, making it relevant to networked information systems (cs.NI).
